  <prompt>
    Add new enum value `NodeType.DeliverComposite` (ordinal append; do NOT renumber existing values — preserve `AIAnalysis = 100_000_000`, `Output = 100_000_001`, etc.) and extend `PlaybookExecutionEngine` to handle composite Output nodes. A composite node accepts N upstream Action node outputs keyed by `sectionName` (declared in `sprk_configjson` per the existing Output Node convention) and composes them per consumer destination (workspace widget / form prefill / chat). Existing single-action Output Node behavior MUST remain unchanged when only one upstream is wired — this is the backward-compat invariant (FR-52).
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in the JPS playbook execution engine + multi-node DAG orchestration.</role>

  <goal>
    `NodeType.DeliverComposite` enum value added at the end of the existing enum (preserving ordinals); `PlaybookExecutionEngine` resolves composite nodes by gathering N upstream Action outputs keyed by declared `sectionName`, emits per-section results to downstream consumers. Unit test executes a composite node with 3 Action upstreams and asserts the SSE event sequence shows 3 `section_data` events keyed by section name. Single-upstream Output Node test (legacy) continues to pass unchanged.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-52 + Phase 5R "Multi-node Output composition" cluster. The current Output Node model couples schema declaration with the Action (schema-on-action) AND a schema-aware widget, creating 5 coordination points to keep in sync. Composite Output collapses this to 2 (section name + section state) by routing N Action outputs into ONE composite Output Node keyed by section name. This task lands the engine surface only — per-section SSE (114a), widget rework (114b), ADR (114c), and the per-playbook migration (118R) follow.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookExecutionEngine.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/INodeExecutor.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/NodeService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookOrchestrationService.cs</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/PlaybookExecutionEngineTests.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-52">Single-upstream Output Node behavior unchanged (backward-compat invariant).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-52">Composite node MUST emit one section per upstream Action keyed by declared `sectionName`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Stays in `Services/Ai/` boundary; no CRUD-code violations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">No file content in telemetry; metadata-only orchestration logs.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement; report delta vs current baseline (~45.65 MB).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">Streaming preservation — Path 3 chat-summarize streaming behavior unchanged.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Backward-compat invariant: existing schema-position playbooks continue to work via `FieldDelta` until migrated by 118R.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Component justification — extending existing `PlaybookExecutionEngine` (NFR-A5 wire-not-build); NO new orchestrator class introduced.</constraint>
  </constraints>

