  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `INodeExecutor.cs` lines 59-80 — confirm current `NodeType` enum shape (`AIAnalysis = 100_000_000`, `Output = 100_000_001`, control flow values). Append new value `DeliverComposite = 100_000_00X` at the END (next available ordinal).</step>
    <step order="2">Read `PlaybookExecutionEngine.cs` — locate the existing `Output` node handler. Understand how upstream Action outputs are currently collected, composed, and dispatched to consumers (widget / chat / form-prefill).</step>
    <step order="3">Read `NodeService.cs` to confirm how nodes are resolved by type at runtime; identify the dispatch switch / map that needs the new composite branch.</step>
    <step order="4">Design the composite handler: gather all upstream Action outputs from the current execution context; read `sprk_configjson` to extract the `sectionName` declared per upstream wire; build a `Dictionary&lt;string, SectionResult&gt;` keyed by section name.</step>
    <step order="5">Implement the composite node executor: emit per-section results as they complete (ordering by completion, NOT by declaration) — wire to the streaming surface that 114a will formalize. For this task, internal output API only; SSE wire-up lands in 114a.</step>
    <step order="6">Add backward-compat guard: if the Output node has only one upstream Action wired AND `NodeType == Output` (not `DeliverComposite`), preserve today's behavior unchanged. Composite logic ONLY runs on `NodeType.DeliverComposite`.</step>
    <step order="7">Grep all `NodeType` switch / pattern-match sites; add `DeliverComposite` handling where appropriate (or document why a site does not need the new case — e.g., scope validation paths inherit from `Output`).</step>
    <step order="8">Add a new unit test in `PlaybookExecutionEngineTests.cs`: build a composite-node playbook fixture with 3 mock Action upstreams emitting `sectionName=A`, `sectionName=B`, `sectionName=C`; execute; assert 3 section results returned keyed by name; assert no schema-position coupling.</step>
    <step order="9">Add a second test asserting backward-compat: a single-action Output Node (legacy `NodeType.Output`, ONE upstream) emits identical output to today (snapshot the existing test output).</step>
    <step order="10">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` + `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`. Existing playbook engine tests pass unmodified; both new tests pass.</step>
    <step order="11">Measure BFF publish size; report delta vs current baseline (~45.65 MB) in `notes/handoffs/114R-bff-publish-delta.md`. Threshold: ≥+5 MB → escalate per CLAUDE.md §10.</step>
    <step order="12">code-review + adr-check (Step 9.5 quality gates).</step>
    <step order="13">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 114R → ✅; current-task.md → ready for 114a.</step>
  </steps>

