  <notes>
    Wave 5-C anchor task — THE BIG ONE of Phase 5R. This task lands the engine surface only; per-section SSE wire-up (114a) consumes the per-section output API introduced here. Tasks 114a → 114b → 114c → 118R depend on this in sequence (114b is FE-only parallel-safe after 114a contract locks). Use enum APPEND (do NOT renumber) to preserve binary compat for any persisted ordinal references. SSE event names (`section_started`, `section_data`, `section_completed`) are formalized in 114a — this task may emit them internally but the contract is owned by 114a.
